Claude 4.8 on 2026-06-21 at ~23:05:
Hunted the bugs with a faithful port of the lighting math plus instrumentation of the real render.

Root cause of "lighting through logo parts": face lighting from REGION points passed NO occluder (occ=null), and exterior lighting occluded only by the OTHER b — so a point lit whole faces straight through intervening logo (and through its own b). This is the region-6 bug: side1-right lit 11/11 (the whole element) instead of the sliver. Fix: accFace now takes a LIST of occluders and skips any sample whose ray crosses a b silhouette; region AND exterior face lighting now occlude by BOTH b silhouettes (self + other). The ray ends ON the lit face — an edge of its own silhouette — but segInt's open interval ignores the endpoint touch, so only a genuine intervening crossing blocks. Verified: region-6 -> side1-right now lit 4/11 (the corner-4/11 window) instead of 11/11.

Mouth group: added side1-right (#3, inner first side seen through the mouth) -> B_G_MOUTH=[1,13,11,8,3], and updated b-out-mouth_face.svg to show it. On the "between tips" capture I instrumented the real code: BOTH tips actually light (tip-top-right on the mouth-facing b, tip-top-left on the other), so the dead tip is config-specific occlusion, not a code bug; with occlusion now correct + side1-right added, each point lights exactly what it sees.

onEl reach: +50% -> ONEL_REACH = 31.5·KLOGO·scale (≈1.5 annulus thicknesses).

No console errors. Wrapped up iteration9: saved the six captures into the iteration folder, wrote interaction_2026_06_21.md (full exchange), and rendered gallery/iteration009.png at the fixed 1024×1006 frame.
